{
  "texts": [
    "While supervised rule-based methods relying on keywords (potentially weighted by importance) offer a clear pipeline from the definition of rules to the final output, more recent systems-especially large language models-remain largely opaque.",
    "This \"black box\" nature can hinder reproducibility, as subtle differences in how text is embedded or vectorized may alter downstream results.",
    "Researchers must therefore confront important questions about how dependent their conclusions are on the specific model selected, and about how to evaluate the robustness of their results.",
    "Conceptually, a measure of similarity would require some form of formal statistical inference.",
    "One can think of a true underlying relationship variable, x, that might take values {0, 1}."
  ]
}